WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:15.056 --> 00:00:16.933
{\an8}Hold all my calls.

2
00:00:24.399 --> 00:00:26.025
♪ <i>Christmas. Christmas</i> ♪

3
00:00:26.109 --> 00:00:27.318
♪ <i>Christmas. Christmas</i> ♪

4
00:00:27.402 --> 00:00:29.112
{\an8}♪ <i>Christmas. Christmas</i> ♪

5
00:00:29.195 --> 00:00:31.322
{\an8}Girls. it's time.

6
00:00:31.406 --> 00:00:32.449
Dad. no.

7
00:00:32.532 --> 00:00:36.870
I have to keep feeding the Christmas Panda
or the Panda will die.

8
00:00:36.953 --> 00:00:41.541
His death is on your conscience.
I hope bedtime was worth it.

9
00:00:41.624 --> 00:00:43.376
Who said bedtime?

10
00:00:43.460 --> 00:00:47.547
It's time for the grand finale
of Templeton Christmas Traditions.

11
00:00:47.630 --> 00:00:51.259
Dad tells a holiday-themed story
until you fall asleep. Whoo!

12
00:00:51.342 --> 00:00:54.095
Do we have to?
I'm in the middle of something.

13
00:00:54.179 --> 00:00:56.890
Christmas. Christmas. Christmas... Hey.

14
00:00:57.432 --> 00:01:01.478
Why do we have to do something
just because it's a tradition?

15
00:01:02.270 --> 00:01:05.273
{\an8}I know someone
who felt the same way you did.

16
00:01:05.356 --> 00:01:07.901
Who? Do I know them? Do they have a beard?

17
00:01:07.984 --> 00:01:10.028
Or a curse that makes them sing?

18
00:01:10.111 --> 00:01:12.363
It was actually your Uncle Ted.

19
00:01:12.447 --> 00:01:13.990
And once upon a time...

20
00:01:14.574 --> 00:01:16.201
Sneaky story intro.

21
00:01:16.284 --> 00:01:19.954
When he was a baby.
he hated our Christmas traditions.

22
00:01:20.038 --> 00:01:23.792
even though they were
the most awesome traditions ever.

23
00:01:23.875 --> 00:01:26.294
<i>Five days before Christmas. we played...</i>

24
00:01:26.377 --> 00:01:28.880
Shock That Elf.

25
00:01:28.963 --> 00:01:31.508
- It's your dad's year to be the elf.
- All right.

26
00:01:31.591 --> 00:01:34.803
But me and my elf buddy here
are pretty hard to...

27
00:01:34.886 --> 00:01:36.221
Merry Christmas.

28
00:01:39.891 --> 00:01:44.646
<i>Four days before Christmas.
we'd make cards for our grandparents.</i>

29
00:01:44.729 --> 00:01:46.147
A Christmas tree.

30
00:01:47.232 --> 00:01:48.191
A reindeer.

31
00:01:50.401 --> 00:01:52.695
The baby made Santa's sleigh.

32
00:01:53.238 --> 00:01:56.699
<i>Three days before Christmas.
we'd sing the most soulful</i>

33
00:01:56.783 --> 00:01:58.576
<i>bass-and-glockenspiel rendition</i>

34
00:01:58.660 --> 00:02:01.121
<i>of "The Night Before Christmas"
you've ever heard.</i>

35
00:02:01.204 --> 00:02:04.707
<i>♪ 'Twas the night before Christmas
And all through the house ♪</i>

36
00:02:04.791 --> 00:02:09.129
<i>♪ Not a creature was stirring
Not even a mouse ♪</i>

37
00:02:11.005 --> 00:02:13.633
<i>Two days before
Uncle Ted's first Christmas.</i>

38
00:02:13.716 --> 00:02:15.718
<i>that's when the magic started.</i>

39
00:02:15.802 --> 00:02:17.303
Work with me. baby.

40
00:02:17.887 --> 00:02:20.723
Aw. there. Our handsome little elf.

41
00:02:20.807 --> 00:02:22.600
Ooh! I'm gonna grab the camera.

42
00:02:26.020 --> 00:02:28.356
I thought Christmas was a day.
not a month.

43
00:02:28.439 --> 00:02:31.151
You can't contain
Templeton traditions to one day.

44
00:02:31.234 --> 00:02:34.028
That's like trying to hold eight ants.
Too many ants.

45
00:02:34.112 --> 00:02:37.699
You performed "The Night Before Christmas"
three days before.

46
00:02:37.782 --> 00:02:41.077
Performing it on the actual night
before Christmas is bad luck.

47
00:02:42.954 --> 00:02:45.540
Uh. you put a gingerbread fellow
in my pocket?

48
00:02:45.623 --> 00:02:47.500
Because it is good luck.

49
00:02:47.584 --> 00:02:49.627
And yet I'm still here.

50
00:02:49.711 --> 00:02:51.337
wearing this.

51
00:02:51.963 --> 00:02:53.047
Where's yours?

52
00:02:53.131 --> 00:02:56.926
Not participating in today's
"dress like a court jester" tradition?

53
00:02:57.010 --> 00:02:59.304
That's not today's tradition. We...

54
00:02:59.888 --> 00:03:03.600
Who's ready
to get their pictures taken with Santa?

55
00:03:08.771 --> 00:03:11.733
I'll be right there
with you the whole time.

56
00:03:11.816 --> 00:03:14.944
We sit on his lap. tell him what we want.

57
00:03:15.028 --> 00:03:19.365
It's the easiest and best tradition.
You don't have to freak out.

58
00:03:20.366 --> 00:03:21.200
Danny?

59
00:03:22.327 --> 00:03:23.828
Tim. check this out.

60
00:03:23.912 --> 00:03:24.871
A snowball?

61
00:03:24.954 --> 00:03:27.415
I'm gonna throw it in Santa's face.

62
00:03:27.498 --> 00:03:30.001
What? You'll get on the naughty list.

63
00:03:30.084 --> 00:03:32.462
Oh. I'm always on the naughty list.

64
00:03:32.545 --> 00:03:36.174
I don't give old Kringle the power
to suppress my animal instincts.

65
00:03:36.257 --> 00:03:38.426
But only good kids get presents.

66
00:03:38.509 --> 00:03:39.844
Do only they?

67
00:03:39.928 --> 00:03:42.931
Naughty-listers
get the greatest present of all. coal.

68
00:03:43.014 --> 00:03:45.516
The black rock with a million uses.

69
00:03:45.600 --> 00:03:48.603
Heat. decoration. other. It's a win-win.

70
00:03:48.686 --> 00:03:52.523
Want me to split this in two?
We can totally flank Santa.

71
00:03:52.607 --> 00:03:55.360
No. I work hard to stay on the nice list.

72
00:03:55.443 --> 00:03:58.071
Who do you think gave them quarters
for massages?

73
00:04:02.575 --> 00:04:03.534
Suit yourself.

74
00:04:05.870 --> 00:04:07.997
We should probably get up.

75
00:04:08.081 --> 00:04:11.125
I've been trying to.

76
00:04:13.878 --> 00:04:14.879
Come on up.

77
00:04:19.092 --> 00:04:21.386
Timothy Templeton. Four T's in it.

78
00:04:21.469 --> 00:04:24.430
This is Theodore.
Same last name. one less T.

79
00:04:24.973 --> 00:04:25.807
Boss Baby.

80
00:04:26.557 --> 00:04:27.392
Ron.

81
00:04:27.475 --> 00:04:29.727
Um. what is happening?

82
00:04:29.811 --> 00:04:32.814
We used to work together. a long time ago.

83
00:04:32.897 --> 00:04:34.565
Wait. Santa is...

84
00:04:34.649 --> 00:04:35.900
Former Baby Corp.

85
00:04:35.984 --> 00:04:39.153
As disloyal as a cat
with trade secrets to sell.

86
00:04:39.237 --> 00:04:40.905
Oh. Boss Baby.

87
00:04:40.989 --> 00:04:43.533
I'm just trying
to spread joy and happiness.

88
00:04:43.616 --> 00:04:46.536
Blah. blah. blah.
I heard it all the day you quit.

89
00:04:46.619 --> 00:04:48.997
When will Mommy and Daddy take a picture?

90
00:04:49.080 --> 00:04:53.543
- Honey. take a picture.
- I'm trying. I'm just so relaxed.

91
00:04:53.626 --> 00:04:56.337
I left Baby Corp because I had this idea

92
00:04:56.421 --> 00:04:59.632
of how to make the world a happier place
with Christmas cheer.

93
00:04:59.716 --> 00:05:00.842
Think it's working?

94
00:05:00.925 --> 00:05:02.135
You're doing fine.

95
00:05:02.218 --> 00:05:04.137
Don't side with this hippie.

96
00:05:04.220 --> 00:05:07.098
He betrayed everything
Baby Corp stands for.

97
00:05:07.181 --> 00:05:10.310
He poached half the company
for his toys-for-nothing program.

98
00:05:10.393 --> 00:05:13.688
And he's exploiting baby labor
to make those toys.

99
00:05:13.771 --> 00:05:15.690
Elves. Elves make the toys.

100
00:05:15.773 --> 00:05:18.109
Oh. come on. That's just marketing.

101
00:05:19.360 --> 00:05:21.446
Whoa. they are babies?

102
00:05:21.529 --> 00:05:23.781
- Okay. say cheese.
- Cheese.

103
00:05:23.865 --> 00:05:25.450
Smile for your parents.

104
00:05:25.533 --> 00:05:28.870
I will never be caught smiling
with a commie like...

105
00:05:29.579 --> 00:05:30.830
Gotcha.

106
00:05:30.913 --> 00:05:32.582
Ho. ho. ho!

107
00:05:32.665 --> 00:05:35.460
I'm on the nice list. right?

108
00:05:36.210 --> 00:05:37.170
Tippy top.

109
00:05:37.253 --> 00:05:40.965
Yes. For Christmas. I want
Football Mike Canadian Football Edition

110
00:05:41.049 --> 00:05:42.967
with the locker room Jacuzzi playset.

111
00:05:43.051 --> 00:05:46.220
You write that request
in official letter form?

112
00:05:46.304 --> 00:05:48.097
Now he loves paperwork.

113
00:05:48.181 --> 00:05:49.265
You know it.

114
00:05:49.348 --> 00:05:53.061
Drop it off with my elves.
and have a Merry Christmas.

115
00:05:53.144 --> 00:05:55.271
Thanks. Santa. You too. bye.

116
00:06:00.068 --> 00:06:02.111
I see you. Danny Petrosky.

117
00:06:02.195 --> 00:06:04.447
Naughty list life forever.

118
00:06:06.365 --> 00:06:08.993
See? Wasn't that fun. little guy?

119
00:06:09.077 --> 00:06:13.289
Look. Cracklin' Bones O'Dell
and the Caroling Cracklettes.

120
00:06:13.372 --> 00:06:15.166
Ho. ho. ho!

121
00:06:15.249 --> 00:06:17.627
Put me down. I have a score to settle.

122
00:06:17.710 --> 00:06:20.421
You won't do anything
to get me on the naughty list?

123
00:06:20.505 --> 00:06:22.632
I'm not a monster. Templeton.

124
00:06:23.633 --> 00:06:25.593
Santa Claus is.

125
00:06:26.844 --> 00:06:29.680
So. Ron. you like getting mail?

126
00:06:31.516 --> 00:06:33.893
Well. here's a special delivery.

127
00:06:38.439 --> 00:06:40.316
Huh?

128
00:07:03.089 --> 00:07:07.301
Not like you to be sleeping on the job
on Christmas Eve. Dongle.

129
00:07:07.385 --> 00:07:09.887
It's Christmas Eve? Where am...? Oh!

130
00:07:09.971 --> 00:07:14.016
You still owe me 300 hollyberries.
Dongle. Pay up.

131
00:07:14.100 --> 00:07:16.436
Why are you calling me...? Where...?

132
00:07:16.519 --> 00:07:17.353
Oh. no.

133
00:07:17.437 --> 00:07:19.564
Don't play dumb. Dongle.

134
00:07:19.647 --> 00:07:22.150
I want my money before Boxing Day. Get it?

135
00:07:22.233 --> 00:07:23.734
Do get it. Not Dongle.

136
00:07:23.818 --> 00:07:27.822
Dongle! I'm so jolly to see you.

137
00:07:27.905 --> 00:07:29.157
Not Dongle.

138
00:07:29.240 --> 00:07:32.076
What's up with your voice. Dongle?
Are you sick?

139
00:07:33.035 --> 00:07:35.079
I'm not Dongle.

140
00:07:35.163 --> 00:07:36.664
Everybody. come quick.

141
00:07:36.747 --> 00:07:37.707
Dongle's sick.

142
00:07:40.460 --> 00:07:41.419
Dongle.

143
00:07:41.502 --> 00:07:43.504
Can you see? Look at me.

144
00:07:43.588 --> 00:07:45.089
I'm not Dongle!

145
00:07:46.674 --> 00:07:47.967
It's Christmas Eve.

146
00:07:48.593 --> 00:07:52.013
- You'll love it.
- Santa. Dongle is sorry for sleep...

147
00:07:54.807 --> 00:07:57.226
Huh?

148
00:07:57.310 --> 00:08:01.522
- What did you do with my brother?
- What did you do with Santa?

149
00:08:01.606 --> 00:08:03.149
Oh. no. Are you...?

150
00:08:03.232 --> 00:08:06.861
Dongle's name is Ding Dong Dongle.

151
00:08:06.944 --> 00:08:08.946
Yeah. but you're an elf?

152
00:08:09.030 --> 00:08:11.449
Superior toymaker of the North Pole.

153
00:08:11.532 --> 00:08:14.327
When Dongle makes a toy.
so many jaws drop to the floor

154
00:08:14.410 --> 00:08:17.246
that the jaw doctor can buy a new mansion.

155
00:08:17.330 --> 00:08:20.041
You made a rocking horse from the crib?

156
00:08:20.124 --> 00:08:21.667
Is it perfect?

157
00:08:21.751 --> 00:08:22.752
Then yes.

158
00:08:22.835 --> 00:08:26.297
Wait. so if you're here.
then my brother is...

159
00:08:26.380 --> 00:08:31.260
At the North Pole. of course.
Does Dongle look like he is from Texas?

160
00:08:31.344 --> 00:08:33.804
Imagine cowboy hat Dongle.

161
00:08:34.430 --> 00:08:35.431
Very handsome.

162
00:08:35.515 --> 00:08:37.934
So he's with Santa? Aw.

163
00:08:38.017 --> 00:08:39.852
We gotta get him back now.

164
00:08:39.936 --> 00:08:43.689
It's his first Christmas.
We have more traditions he has to do.

165
00:08:43.773 --> 00:08:45.775
Dongle needs to get back now.

166
00:08:45.858 --> 00:08:48.694
Or the world will be bombarded
with inferior toys

167
00:08:48.778 --> 00:08:50.863
that blacken children's hearts.

168
00:08:50.947 --> 00:08:53.783
My brother works at Baby Corp. so all we...

169
00:08:53.866 --> 00:08:57.495
Baby Corp.
Can't make toys to save their lives.

170
00:08:57.578 --> 00:08:59.622
Does that situation come up a lot?

171
00:09:00.248 --> 00:09:02.667
Dongle could tell you stories.

172
00:09:02.750 --> 00:09:04.293
Yes. please. But later.

173
00:09:04.377 --> 00:09:07.463
Baby Corp is our only hope
to get out of this.

174
00:09:07.547 --> 00:09:09.840
Jimbo. Staci. we have a situation.

175
00:09:09.924 --> 00:09:12.468
T-W-A-F-E-R.

176
00:09:12.552 --> 00:09:13.386
TWAFER.

177
00:09:14.804 --> 00:09:17.807
"Tommy wants a fire engine. red."

178
00:09:17.890 --> 00:09:20.142
TWAFER. TWAFER.

179
00:09:20.226 --> 00:09:21.477
Not now. Dongle.

180
00:09:21.561 --> 00:09:23.896
I'm not Dongle. Ron.

181
00:09:23.980 --> 00:09:27.066
Boss Baby?
What the jingles are you doing here?

182
00:09:27.149 --> 00:09:30.444
The question is.
how the jingles do I get out of here?

183
00:09:30.528 --> 00:09:34.699
Oh. I'd love to help.
but I'm memorizing letters.

184
00:09:34.782 --> 00:09:40.079
If I don't get their requests locked down.
it'll take me weeks to deliver gifts.

185
00:09:40.162 --> 00:09:42.373
Speaking of jingles. "jingle."

186
00:09:42.456 --> 00:09:47.795
"Judy is now getting lavender earmuffs."
J-I-N-G-L-E. JINGLE.

187
00:09:47.878 --> 00:09:51.465
You're an embarrassment to efficiency.
Get a computer.

188
00:09:51.549 --> 00:09:54.510
The elves and I
are like a family business.

189
00:09:54.594 --> 00:09:56.804
They make the toys. I do this.

190
00:09:56.887 --> 00:09:59.265
These are our family traditions.

191
00:09:59.348 --> 00:10:02.602
and they've made everyone happy
for a long time.

192
00:10:02.685 --> 00:10:06.355
Yay for your family.
Take me home to mine. Big Beard.

193
00:10:07.231 --> 00:10:11.068
I'm busy. I'll take you tonight
when I deliver presents.

194
00:10:11.152 --> 00:10:13.112
What do I do in the meantime?

195
00:10:13.696 --> 00:10:15.114
Help make a few toys.

196
00:10:15.197 --> 00:10:18.117
and maybe learn
about the Christmas spirit.

197
00:10:21.829 --> 00:10:25.666
- Any word on rescuing my brother?
- Sorry. ran into a snag.

198
00:10:26.375 --> 00:10:28.794
Typical Baby Corp incompetence.

199
00:10:31.547 --> 00:10:33.299
Typical Dongle excellence.

200
00:10:33.382 --> 00:10:36.177
I won that trophy
for excellence in trophy modeling.

201
00:10:36.260 --> 00:10:39.555
Stop making stuff out of stuff.
What's the snag?

202
00:10:39.639 --> 00:10:43.309
Chupie tech is jammed at the North Pole.
Stupid Santa Claus.

203
00:10:43.392 --> 00:10:45.853
Watch your mouth. Baby Corp mongrel.

204
00:10:49.231 --> 00:10:52.818
It's less than 24 hours
until my brother's first Christmas.

205
00:10:52.902 --> 00:10:56.447
If we can't chupie there.
we have to find another way.

206
00:10:57.031 --> 00:10:59.116
Mom and Dad will be worried sick.

207
00:10:59.200 --> 00:11:02.620
You relax.
Dongle will take care of everything.

208
00:11:02.703 --> 00:11:07.041
This one's from Aunt Dorothy.
"Merry Christmas from Aunt Dorothy."

209
00:11:07.124 --> 00:11:09.210
Oh. that's nice.

210
00:11:09.293 --> 00:11:10.336
Is that a grenade?

211
00:11:10.419 --> 00:11:13.839
Don't be foolish.
Dongle doesn't explode parents.

212
00:11:13.923 --> 00:11:16.300
Dongle kills with poison gas.

213
00:11:16.384 --> 00:11:17.218
What?

214
00:11:18.552 --> 00:11:20.012
Do you smell?

215
00:11:23.391 --> 00:11:25.142
Dongle told a sick joke.

216
00:11:25.226 --> 00:11:29.939
This is Santa's sleeping dust
for when the children stay up to see him.

217
00:11:30.022 --> 00:11:31.190
What the heck?

218
00:11:31.273 --> 00:11:34.318
Drama is the spice of life.

219
00:11:35.903 --> 00:11:38.656
Should give us time
to get to the North Pole and back.

220
00:11:38.739 --> 00:11:40.157
But with them asleep.

221
00:11:40.241 --> 00:11:44.453
I have to do the shopping
for our traditional fruitcake hockey.

222
00:11:44.537 --> 00:11:48.040
Which we play while wearing Hawaiian leis
made from snacks. So fun.

223
00:11:48.624 --> 00:11:50.709
Point is. we need to move fast.

224
00:11:50.793 --> 00:11:54.588
No sweat.
Santa has magic portals in every mall.

225
00:11:54.672 --> 00:11:56.966
They appear every night
after business hours.

226
00:11:57.049 --> 00:11:59.844
but only until 9 a.m.
the day before Christmas.

227
00:11:59.927 --> 00:12:01.262
We have 20 minutes.

228
00:12:01.345 --> 00:12:03.347
Why didn't you tell us before?

229
00:12:03.431 --> 00:12:09.061
Were you not paying attention when Dongle
told you drama is the spice of life?

230
00:12:20.573 --> 00:12:23.284
So this is where Christmas comes from?

231
00:12:23.367 --> 00:12:24.201
You bet.

232
00:12:24.285 --> 00:12:27.913
We got Jingly Jangly there
doing wrapping paper design.

233
00:12:27.997 --> 00:12:30.249
Ribbon testing with Tippy Tappy Sloppy.

234
00:12:30.332 --> 00:12:32.501
Okay. okay. that one is good.

235
00:12:32.585 --> 00:12:36.088
Lala Doo-Da and Diddly Doo
write all the best carols.

236
00:12:36.172 --> 00:12:39.425
What kind of nog-house
open-mic garbage is that?

237
00:12:39.508 --> 00:12:43.012
You wouldn't know a hit
if it knocked your tooth out.

238
00:12:43.095 --> 00:12:48.142
And of course. toy-making with me.
PoopyDoopy. filling in for Dongle.

239
00:12:48.225 --> 00:12:50.436
I admire your skill.

240
00:12:50.519 --> 00:12:51.479
Why thank you.

241
00:12:51.562 --> 00:12:55.441
But I can't help noticing
inefficiencies in your systems.

242
00:12:55.524 --> 00:12:56.358
What?

243
00:12:56.442 --> 00:13:00.863
I notice you make all your gingerbread
from the eggs of a single goose?

244
00:13:02.615 --> 00:13:06.535
That's not just a goose.
She's Ginger the Gingergoose.

245
00:13:06.619 --> 00:13:09.371
Sure. And dare I ask a follow-up?

246
00:13:09.455 --> 00:13:13.209
Why have those elves been rubbing gumdrops
on the egg for two hours?

247
00:13:13.292 --> 00:13:16.754
To make it the best gingerbread
in the whole world.

248
00:13:16.837 --> 00:13:18.214
Dubious claim.

249
00:13:18.297 --> 00:13:19.131
Try this.

250
00:13:19.924 --> 00:13:21.175
Mm.

251
00:13:21.675 --> 00:13:24.386
This is really good. What's the secret?

252
00:13:24.470 --> 00:13:29.141
It's made with store-bought chicken eggs
and was stuffed in my pocket.

253
00:13:31.185 --> 00:13:32.520
Delicious.

254
00:13:33.270 --> 00:13:34.772
You guys get it now?

255
00:13:34.855 --> 00:13:37.900
We need
to put our gingerbread in your pocket.

256
00:13:37.983 --> 00:13:40.361
No. my point is efficiency.

257
00:13:40.444 --> 00:13:44.615
You can't mess up gingerbread.
Just crack eggs in some batter.

258
00:13:45.824 --> 00:13:48.869
Why does this goose
even have a job. right. Ginger?

259
00:13:48.953 --> 00:13:52.164
What else needs fixing around here?

260
00:13:59.755 --> 00:14:03.759
You're watching paint dry?
I thought you were on a deadline.

261
00:14:03.842 --> 00:14:08.514
- We take pride in our wrapping paper.
- Just to be torn open?

262
00:14:08.597 --> 00:14:09.974
You're wasting time.

263
00:14:10.057 --> 00:14:13.018
But this is the way
we've always done things.

264
00:14:13.102 --> 00:14:14.103
Not anymore.

265
00:14:14.186 --> 00:14:15.563
Whee!

266
00:14:16.647 --> 00:14:19.733
Boom. efficiency. Hit me with another one.

267
00:14:21.026 --> 00:14:22.987
Carol writers. right?

268
00:14:23.070 --> 00:14:24.446
Supposed to be.

269
00:14:24.530 --> 00:14:28.409
But Diddly Doo overdid it
on the milk and cookies again.

270
00:14:28.492 --> 00:14:30.744
Well. excuse me. Mother.

271
00:14:30.828 --> 00:14:32.997
You ever feel like working?

272
00:14:33.080 --> 00:14:34.665
We'll work when I tell you.

273
00:14:35.624 --> 00:14:37.501
If I can make a suggestion... Oh!

274
00:14:38.043 --> 00:14:40.254
Don't mess with our creative process.

275
00:14:40.337 --> 00:14:42.631
You've got the talent of a wreath.

276
00:14:44.008 --> 00:14:46.176
They're fine. What else you got?

277
00:14:49.471 --> 00:14:51.223
I'm not laughing. Toss it.

278
00:14:53.267 --> 00:14:54.727
Spin me up on this nonsense.

279
00:14:54.810 --> 00:14:58.022
Everyone knows.
ribbon is no good if it doesn't tickle me.

280
00:14:58.105 --> 00:14:59.648
I don't think that's true.

281
00:14:59.732 --> 00:15:00.900
Oh. but it is.

282
00:15:00.983 --> 00:15:01.859
No. it's not.

283
00:15:01.942 --> 00:15:04.111
Pretty sure it is.

284
00:15:10.868 --> 00:15:11.994
He's a genius.

285
00:15:12.077 --> 00:15:15.456
Could it be. everything
we've been doing has been wrong?

286
00:15:15.539 --> 00:15:17.458
No telling. but yes.

287
00:15:17.541 --> 00:15:18.959
Please. walk with me.

288
00:15:19.043 --> 00:15:23.255
A walk-and-talk? You're getting
the hang of this efficiency thing.

289
00:15:23.339 --> 00:15:24.340
You're telling me.

290
00:15:24.423 --> 00:15:28.093
You've been here an hour.
and our productivity is up 20 percent.

291
00:15:28.177 --> 00:15:31.889
We might actually get a nog break
before Santa leaves.

292
00:15:31.972 --> 00:15:35.643
Why settle for nog?
Imagine what else you could have.

293
00:15:35.726 --> 00:15:38.771
<i>Computers for
naughty/nice cross-reference.</i>

294
00:15:38.854 --> 00:15:41.982
<i>Industrial ovens
for mass gingerbread baking.</i>

295
00:15:42.066 --> 00:15:44.777
<i>Break rooms full of gumdrop delights.</i>

296
00:15:44.860 --> 00:15:47.738
<i>And of course. mahogany crafters' lamps.</i>

297
00:15:47.821 --> 00:15:50.324
Yes. to ward off snow monsters.

298
00:15:50.407 --> 00:15:52.368
Mahogany lamps ward off snow monsters?

299
00:15:52.451 --> 00:15:53.410
Mahogany does.

300
00:15:53.494 --> 00:15:56.580
Weird. I was just trying
to class up the joint.

301
00:15:56.664 --> 00:15:59.458
<i>We should redo
this entire floor in mahogany.</i>

302
00:15:59.541 --> 00:16:02.419
Mahogany? No. Why?

303
00:16:05.839 --> 00:16:10.052
It'd help Christmas cheer
if no one was eaten by a snow monster.

304
00:16:10.135 --> 00:16:13.597
These reforms will take
an upfront investment.

305
00:16:13.681 --> 00:16:15.099
What's your cash on hand?

306
00:16:15.182 --> 00:16:17.935
Fifty trillion hollyberries.

307
00:16:18.018 --> 00:16:19.770
- In dollars?
- Seven.

308
00:16:19.853 --> 00:16:21.939
Okay. we need to raise revenue.

309
00:16:22.022 --> 00:16:24.316
What do you charge
to get on the nice list?

310
00:16:24.400 --> 00:16:26.652
The only charge is
being the best you can...

311
00:16:26.735 --> 00:16:27.820
Honk. honk.

312
00:16:27.903 --> 00:16:31.907
You sillies are practically
feeding cash to the reindeer.

313
00:16:31.991 --> 00:16:34.284
But it's always been free.

314
00:16:34.368 --> 00:16:38.122
And your boss always wears
a red suit to a home invasion.

315
00:16:38.205 --> 00:16:40.416
Tradition's a dumb reason to do anything.

316
00:16:40.499 --> 00:16:44.253
You're running a business
that's stalled out below its potential.

317
00:16:44.336 --> 00:16:45.754
It's killing my soul.

318
00:16:45.838 --> 00:16:47.464
But good news?

319
00:16:47.548 --> 00:16:49.008
You've got me.

320
00:16:50.342 --> 00:16:51.218
The portal.

321
00:16:51.301 --> 00:16:53.303
What? Yes. Hurry up. let's go.

322
00:16:54.388 --> 00:16:56.807
Unmade toys. Dongle is coming.

323
00:16:58.308 --> 00:17:00.060
No.

324
00:17:00.144 --> 00:17:01.937
You had to stop at the snack cart?

325
00:17:02.021 --> 00:17:03.647
I'm pulling double duty.

326
00:17:03.731 --> 00:17:08.318
I have to rescue my brother
and keep my family traditions from dying.

327
00:17:08.402 --> 00:17:12.698
Stop being so dramatic.
There has to be a simple solution.

328
00:17:13.365 --> 00:17:15.868
Four plane tickets to the North Pole.

329
00:17:16.493 --> 00:17:18.912
Great. Does anyone have $11.000?

330
00:17:18.996 --> 00:17:20.873
I have 700 hollyberries.

331
00:17:20.956 --> 00:17:22.708
I had to buy a winter hat.

332
00:17:24.543 --> 00:17:26.587
I only have 10K five hunny.

333
00:17:26.670 --> 00:17:27.796
So close.

334
00:17:30.382 --> 00:17:33.135
Look. super speedy delivery.

335
00:17:33.218 --> 00:17:37.723
"Santa letters and packages delivered
to the North Pole before midnight"?

336
00:17:37.806 --> 00:17:41.018
We follow
the next delivery truck to the airport.

337
00:17:41.101 --> 00:17:44.063
sneak on a jet
disguised as food-service workers.

338
00:17:44.146 --> 00:17:46.356
When the crew asks. "Is that low-fat?"

339
00:17:46.440 --> 00:17:48.275
I go. "No. it's high fist."

340
00:17:48.358 --> 00:17:50.527
Double thumpers into a roundhouse kick.

341
00:17:50.611 --> 00:17:53.822
We've put two on the ground.
because I'm good at kicking.

342
00:17:53.906 --> 00:17:57.534
But we can't control the cockpit
until we defeat six crooked co-pilots.

343
00:17:57.618 --> 00:18:00.162
each trained in a deadly martial art.

344
00:18:00.871 --> 00:18:02.539
My plan was better.

345
00:18:02.623 --> 00:18:04.958
Oh! Watch your elbows. Jimbo.

346
00:18:05.042 --> 00:18:07.294
Dongle. don't eat all my snacks.

347
00:18:07.377 --> 00:18:09.922
Dongle is not eating anything.

348
00:18:10.005 --> 00:18:12.508
I hear little Chloe
is on the naughty list...

349
00:18:12.591 --> 00:18:14.927
What's it worth to you
to get Josie into nice?

350
00:18:15.010 --> 00:18:17.805
Start Scooter on the $50 nice package...

351
00:18:17.888 --> 00:18:20.849
Isn't everything more beautiful
when it's profitable?

352
00:18:20.933 --> 00:18:22.768
This makes me feel yucky.

353
00:18:22.851 --> 00:18:25.896
like a sticky candy cane
that fell on a floor.

354
00:18:25.979 --> 00:18:30.067
Remember. you're helping
to finance more efficient toy-making.

355
00:18:30.150 --> 00:18:32.486
Things are looking up
for your compensation.

356
00:18:32.569 --> 00:18:35.280
We're gonna get more Christmas cheer?

357
00:18:35.364 --> 00:18:38.951
- You get paid in Christmas cheer?
- I wish.

358
00:18:39.034 --> 00:18:40.702
We get paid in twinkly smiles.

359
00:18:40.786 --> 00:18:43.622
which can be exchanged
for Christmas cheer.

360
00:18:43.705 --> 00:18:45.707
You have to trade in at the Santa shop.

361
00:18:45.791 --> 00:18:48.794
They're only open
for a half-hour on Thursdays.

362
00:18:48.877 --> 00:18:52.923
Unless you send your smiles
by penguin messenger. which takes months.

363
00:18:53.006 --> 00:18:56.343
What kind of hustle
is Santa running on you?

364
00:18:56.426 --> 00:18:59.304
We love Santa.
We're like a family business.

365
00:18:59.388 --> 00:19:03.100
Are you? I know Dasher
and Dancer and Prancer and Vixen.

366
00:19:03.183 --> 00:19:07.062
All the reindeer do for 364 days a year
is eat grass and poop.

367
00:19:07.146 --> 00:19:10.983
You elves do all the work.
and I couldn't name one of you.

368
00:19:11.066 --> 00:19:12.734
Except you. DookiePoops.

369
00:19:12.818 --> 00:19:15.571
- PoopyDoopy.
- Forget how things have always been done.

370
00:19:15.654 --> 00:19:18.448
What do you deserve right now?

371
00:19:18.532 --> 00:19:21.702
I would like a little recognition.

372
00:19:21.785 --> 00:19:22.619
Yeah.

373
00:19:22.703 --> 00:19:25.622
- Right.
- We should talk to Santa.

374
00:19:26.248 --> 00:19:28.208
Last delivery for the season.

375
00:19:28.292 --> 00:19:32.296
Put it there. right next
to the gigantic pile of letters.

376
00:19:32.379 --> 00:19:34.214
Merry Chri...

377
00:19:34.298 --> 00:19:35.215
We're here.

378
00:19:35.299 --> 00:19:36.967
Good. Dongle is hungry.

379
00:19:37.050 --> 00:19:39.428
Even though Dongle did not eat the snacks.

380
00:19:40.929 --> 00:19:45.017
Uh. you aren't letters to Santa.
I'm disappointed.

381
00:19:45.100 --> 00:19:48.145
But I like feeling disappointed.
so mixed bag.

382
00:19:48.228 --> 00:19:50.981
Remove your funeral suit. sad vampire.

383
00:19:51.064 --> 00:19:52.858
Dongle is here.

384
00:19:52.941 --> 00:19:55.194
Is this the North Pole?

385
00:19:55.277 --> 00:19:58.197
"North Pole." Yay. we're here.

386
00:19:58.280 --> 00:20:01.116
It says "Noth Pole."
You left out the R.

387
00:20:01.200 --> 00:20:06.038
At least I didn't write it backwards.
We could've ended up in Elop Htron.

388
00:20:06.121 --> 00:20:08.081
This is the Noth Pole?

389
00:20:08.165 --> 00:20:10.792
I'm the Noth Pole. That's my name.

390
00:20:10.876 --> 00:20:16.506
I changed it so all the letters to Santa
with that misspelled word come to me.

391
00:20:16.590 --> 00:20:17.674
It's thrilling.

392
00:20:17.758 --> 00:20:21.345
That's a weird thing to be excited about.

393
00:20:21.428 --> 00:20:24.223
Why? This is a pile of hopes and dreams

394
00:20:24.306 --> 00:20:27.226
I can sell to collectors
for a lot of money.

395
00:20:27.309 --> 00:20:31.521
We need to get to the North Pole.
And quick. Is that possible?

396
00:20:31.605 --> 00:20:34.024
It's a 30-minute chartered jet ride.

397
00:20:34.107 --> 00:20:36.777
I can make anything happen.

398
00:20:36.860 --> 00:20:37.945
I'm Noth Pole.

399
00:20:38.028 --> 00:20:39.988
- Yay.
- But I won't.

400
00:20:40.072 --> 00:20:43.283
I don't really feel like it.
Don't touch my pile.

401
00:20:44.034 --> 00:20:45.244
Dongle touched nothing.

402
00:20:45.327 --> 00:20:50.499
These letters go for a fortune in Tokyo.
along with gum chewed by politicians.

403
00:20:50.582 --> 00:20:53.377
industrial blueprints
from mobile home manufacturers...

404
00:20:53.460 --> 00:20:56.255
What happens with
the kids who wrote the letters?

405
00:20:56.338 --> 00:20:59.675
They just don't get
what they want for Christmas.

406
00:20:59.758 --> 00:21:01.426
What? That's horrible.

407
00:21:01.510 --> 00:21:05.347
No. I think you missed it. I get money.

408
00:21:05.430 --> 00:21:07.557
Making money off of Christmas?

409
00:21:07.641 --> 00:21:08.558
That's crazy.

410
00:21:17.734 --> 00:21:18.860
Thank you. boy.

411
00:21:18.944 --> 00:21:22.364
Your shouted words
have inspired me to change...

412
00:21:22.447 --> 00:21:24.992
Yay. it's a Christmas miracle.

413
00:21:25.075 --> 00:21:26.243
...my business model.

414
00:21:26.326 --> 00:21:29.288
When Santa doesn't deliver
and children weep.

415
00:21:29.371 --> 00:21:32.541
parents will do anything
to get them their toys.

416
00:21:32.624 --> 00:21:35.585
even buy them from me at a huge markup.

417
00:21:35.669 --> 00:21:38.005
Don't you use my ideas for evil.

418
00:21:38.088 --> 00:21:41.758
You turned my letters
into a nutcracker in ten seconds?

419
00:21:41.842 --> 00:21:44.094
- No.
- No. him.

420
00:21:44.177 --> 00:21:45.887
Five seconds.

421
00:21:45.971 --> 00:21:49.182
Ten is for lazy toymakers
who are not Dongle.

422
00:21:49.266 --> 00:21:51.518
I like his style.

423
00:21:51.601 --> 00:21:53.228
I've devised a deal.

424
00:21:53.312 --> 00:21:55.397
I'll charter that flight.

425
00:21:55.480 --> 00:22:00.068
but Dongle stays with me
to make 10.000 toys for profit.

426
00:22:00.152 --> 00:22:02.112
No. we're not leaving Dongle.

427
00:22:02.195 --> 00:22:04.364
Go save your brother
with the handsome face

428
00:22:04.448 --> 00:22:06.283
that would look better in glasses.

429
00:22:06.366 --> 00:22:07.784
Dongle will catch up.

430
00:22:07.868 --> 00:22:09.619
- You sure?
- Merry Christmas.

431
00:22:09.703 --> 00:22:13.707
You press that button.
Dongle will get you out of any jam.

432
00:22:13.790 --> 00:22:17.753
Mostly toy-building jams.
That is where the button is of most use.

433
00:22:17.836 --> 00:22:20.797
- Thank you. Dongle.
- Okay. this hug is done.

434
00:22:20.881 --> 00:22:22.341
I'm going to the North Pole.

435
00:22:22.424 --> 00:22:25.761
How do you handle the excitement
of being at the real North Pole?

436
00:22:25.844 --> 00:22:26.970
You don't.

437
00:22:32.225 --> 00:22:34.603
It looks like Baby Corp.

438
00:22:34.686 --> 00:22:36.813
But Christmas-ier.

439
00:22:36.897 --> 00:22:38.440
Let's go over the plan.

440
00:22:38.523 --> 00:22:39.816
Me and Tim look for Boss.

441
00:22:39.900 --> 00:22:44.279
I'll find what they're using to jam
our chupie transport tech. and smash it.

442
00:22:44.362 --> 00:22:45.405
Got that. Tim?

443
00:22:46.323 --> 00:22:49.034
I'm at the North Pole.

444
00:22:49.117 --> 00:22:50.577
Can you keep it together?

445
00:22:50.660 --> 00:22:51.578
No.

446
00:22:52.329 --> 00:22:54.998
I'm actually in Santa Town. I'm gonna...

447
00:22:55.415 --> 00:22:57.793
Um. hello?

448
00:22:57.876 --> 00:22:59.169
Anyone home?

449
00:22:59.252 --> 00:23:01.004
Anyone making toys?

450
00:23:01.088 --> 00:23:02.214
Anyone Santa?

451
00:23:03.840 --> 00:23:05.050
It's gingerbread.

452
00:23:05.133 --> 00:23:08.512
Jimbo. Don't eat the toy factory...

453
00:23:08.595 --> 00:23:11.723
Dang. break me off some of that wall.

454
00:23:11.807 --> 00:23:15.435
Stop chewing.
I hear actual North Pole Christmas Cheer.

455
00:23:15.519 --> 00:23:18.522
Then Santa said.
"Thanks. Tippy Tappy Slappy."

456
00:23:18.605 --> 00:23:22.400
But I'm not Tippy Tappy Slappy.
I'm Tippy Tappy Sloppy.

457
00:23:24.736 --> 00:23:27.280
Ugh. Breaks my heart.

458
00:23:27.364 --> 00:23:31.451
Who's got another complaint
about Santa's mismanagement?

459
00:23:32.119 --> 00:23:34.121
There's the boss. Hi.

460
00:23:35.539 --> 00:23:38.083
We should have suggestion boxes.
but we don't.

461
00:23:38.166 --> 00:23:40.377
So how do we suggest we get one?

462
00:23:41.044 --> 00:23:42.129
What did you do?

463
00:23:42.212 --> 00:23:43.672
Uh. good to see you too.

464
00:23:43.755 --> 00:23:47.717
Where's the fun and jolly toy making?
This is Santa's factory.

465
00:23:47.801 --> 00:23:52.055
Really? It's Santa who clocks in?
Santa who carves the horsies?

466
00:23:52.139 --> 00:23:54.891
Santa spring-loading jack-in-the-boxes?

467
00:23:54.975 --> 00:23:56.518
You're messing with Christmas.

468
00:23:56.601 --> 00:23:58.812
It's a mess. I'm cleaning it up.

469
00:23:58.895 --> 00:24:02.065
Christmas is perfect.
Everyone loves Santa and his elves.

470
00:24:03.984 --> 00:24:05.193
Sorry to interrupt.

471
00:24:05.277 --> 00:24:09.573
We're trying to recall Santa's nicknames.
but couldn't remember.

472
00:24:09.656 --> 00:24:10.740
Can you help us?

473
00:24:10.824 --> 00:24:15.245
Sure. Santa. Santa Clause. St. Nick.
Kriss Kringle. Father Christmas...

474
00:24:15.328 --> 00:24:16.246
Cool. cool.

475
00:24:16.329 --> 00:24:18.623
- Now name an elf.
- What?

476
00:24:18.707 --> 00:24:22.085
You said.
everyone loves Santa and his elves.

477
00:24:22.169 --> 00:24:25.255
You know every single one
of Santa's nicknames.

478
00:24:25.338 --> 00:24:28.091
Surely you know just one of our names.

479
00:24:28.592 --> 00:24:30.051
Uh...

480
00:24:31.094 --> 00:24:32.053
Blitzen?

481
00:24:32.137 --> 00:24:34.306
Blitzen? Blitzen?

482
00:24:34.389 --> 00:24:37.934
Kid's confusing us with
those antlered stink horses?

483
00:24:38.685 --> 00:24:40.020
You done did it now.

484
00:24:41.354 --> 00:24:44.608
I'm done being a cog
in the Christmas wheel.

485
00:24:44.691 --> 00:24:47.319
A wheel we probably made.

486
00:24:47.402 --> 00:24:50.655
Santa's factory? Ha!

487
00:24:50.739 --> 00:24:52.532
This is our factory.

488
00:24:52.616 --> 00:24:54.534
Yeah!

489
00:25:10.258 --> 00:25:11.551
Santa?

490
00:25:12.636 --> 00:25:15.597
How long have you been...
What did you hear?

491
00:25:16.473 --> 00:25:17.515
Enough.

492
00:25:18.266 --> 00:25:20.977
All I wanted was to make everyone happy.

493
00:25:21.061 --> 00:25:23.021
Well. you sure blew that.

494
00:25:24.397 --> 00:25:25.482
Yeah.

495
00:25:29.110 --> 00:25:30.946
We should get better than this.

496
00:25:31.029 --> 00:25:31.988
You're right.

497
00:25:32.739 --> 00:25:34.824
I hope I can do better next year.

498
00:25:37.911 --> 00:25:40.705
{\an8}Not the naughty list.

499
00:25:41.915 --> 00:25:45.335
Santa.

500
00:25:45.418 --> 00:25:47.254
There he is. On his sleigh.

501
00:25:47.837 --> 00:25:49.798
- I can't believe it.
- I know.

502
00:25:49.881 --> 00:25:53.385
He teleported to a sleigh that
would take two minutes to walk to.

503
00:25:53.468 --> 00:25:55.053
Explains the. uh...

504
00:25:55.136 --> 00:25:57.222
No. I can't believe he's gone.

505
00:25:57.305 --> 00:25:59.933
Santa can't go on the naughty list.
He's Santa.

506
00:26:00.016 --> 00:26:02.560
Why does it feel like
a man cave on Mother's Day?

507
00:26:02.644 --> 00:26:04.729
A re-org like this usually takes weeks.

508
00:26:04.813 --> 00:26:06.314
We should be celebrating.

509
00:26:09.276 --> 00:26:10.527
Yeah. get it.

510
00:26:20.495 --> 00:26:22.289
We had a misunderstanding.

511
00:26:22.956 --> 00:26:25.292
Got the chupies working. Let's jet.

512
00:26:25.375 --> 00:26:28.628
Look at that.
Still time to play fruitcake lacrosse.

513
00:26:28.712 --> 00:26:32.090
- Hockey.
- One of those boarding school sports.

514
00:26:32.173 --> 00:26:34.509
What about Santa?
What happens with Christmas?

515
00:26:34.592 --> 00:26:36.970
These elves got it covered.

516
00:26:37.053 --> 00:26:39.472
Uh... Not really.

517
00:26:39.556 --> 00:26:42.309
This was about recognition
for making toys.

518
00:26:42.392 --> 00:26:46.604
Delivering them is Santa's thing.
Because. you know. the sleigh.

519
00:26:46.688 --> 00:26:50.400
This isn't a Santa problem.
It's a logistics problem.

520
00:26:50.483 --> 00:26:52.027
Call in the paper pushers.

521
00:26:52.110 --> 00:26:54.487
Simmons. Hendershot. On my location.

522
00:26:54.571 --> 00:26:58.783
Is this the secret Christmas Party?
Bring on the nog.

523
00:26:58.867 --> 00:27:02.370
- <i>Nog. nog. nog...</i>
- I got something better than nog.

524
00:27:02.454 --> 00:27:06.207
We're gonna solve
Christmas toy delivery logistics.

525
00:27:06.791 --> 00:27:09.169
Yay.

526
00:27:12.130 --> 00:27:14.132
One fire dog. coming up.

527
00:27:16.092 --> 00:27:17.260
This stump taken?

528
00:27:17.844 --> 00:27:19.679
Santa? Why are you...?

529
00:27:20.263 --> 00:27:21.890
Is this about the naughty list?

530
00:27:21.973 --> 00:27:25.018
That snowball to the kisser
should've sealed the deal.

531
00:27:29.689 --> 00:27:33.109
No one is questioning
your naughtiness. or mine.

532
00:27:33.193 --> 00:27:36.613
Whoa. you finally made the jump?

533
00:27:36.696 --> 00:27:39.157
Danny. you've been on my naughty list

534
00:27:39.240 --> 00:27:41.576
since you were old enough
to pass gas at will.

535
00:27:44.162 --> 00:27:45.121
Continue.

536
00:27:45.205 --> 00:27:47.999
I joined the list 20 minutes ago.
and I feel like crud.

537
00:27:48.083 --> 00:27:51.795
But here you are. happy as a clam.
roasting hot dogs on a fire...

538
00:27:51.878 --> 00:27:54.339
Is that last year's bundle of coal?

539
00:27:56.299 --> 00:27:57.592
Doesn't that taste like...

540
00:27:57.675 --> 00:27:58.676
West Virginia?

541
00:27:59.386 --> 00:28:01.012
Oh. yeah.

542
00:28:01.096 --> 00:28:05.517
So how do we live with ourselves
when we've been so naughty?

543
00:28:05.600 --> 00:28:08.812
Papa Noel. I'm glad you asked.

544
00:28:13.108 --> 00:28:16.194
First get rid of this idea
that naughtiness is bad.

545
00:28:16.277 --> 00:28:19.614
Naughty living is very healthy
and very normal.

546
00:28:20.532 --> 00:28:21.741
What? You just...

547
00:28:21.825 --> 00:28:24.452
Got my veggies in the naughtiest way.

548
00:28:25.328 --> 00:28:28.540
Nice needs naughtiness
like night needs day

549
00:28:28.623 --> 00:28:31.459
and turtles need shells
to hide their eyes during scary movies.

550
00:28:32.168 --> 00:28:35.380
Give a naughty man a hotdog.
he'll have a hotdog.

551
00:28:36.464 --> 00:28:41.344
But teach a naughty man to hotdog.
and he'll have a ton of hotdogs.

552
00:28:42.262 --> 00:28:43.179
My ear lobe.

553
00:28:43.263 --> 00:28:45.807
Don't forget. every Christmas morning.

554
00:28:45.890 --> 00:28:49.602
naughty kids wake up to coal.
which is dead dinosaurs.

555
00:28:49.686 --> 00:28:52.772
So while nice kids play with toys...

556
00:28:53.940 --> 00:28:56.526
...we're playing with dead dinosaurs.

557
00:28:56.609 --> 00:28:58.695
And that's rad.

558
00:29:01.448 --> 00:29:03.825
<i>Approaching target.
Open flaps.</i>

559
00:29:03.908 --> 00:29:05.368
Opening flaps.

560
00:29:05.452 --> 00:29:06.661
<i>And release.</i>

561
00:29:15.628 --> 00:29:16.629
Yes. Templeton?

562
00:29:16.713 --> 00:29:20.008
What makes you think
you can do Christmas without Santa?

563
00:29:20.091 --> 00:29:21.926
Uh. the fact that we are.

564
00:29:22.010 --> 00:29:23.845
Let's get industrial fans.

565
00:29:23.928 --> 00:29:26.723
make sure she can handle monsoons
in the South Pacific.

566
00:29:27.724 --> 00:29:30.685
This isn't the same.
You need magic and wonder.

567
00:29:30.769 --> 00:29:33.563
Or Christmas is just
a bonus birthday with a tree.

568
00:29:33.646 --> 00:29:36.107
Yes. but you will get a lot of toys.

569
00:29:36.191 --> 00:29:37.025
- Toys.
- Toys.

570
00:29:37.108 --> 00:29:37.942
- Toys.
- Toys.

571
00:29:38.026 --> 00:29:40.069
There's more to Christmas than toys.

572
00:29:40.153 --> 00:29:44.032
It's how awesome it is
to see boot marks on snowy roofs.

573
00:29:44.115 --> 00:29:46.242
- See if we can fake boot marks.
- On it.

574
00:29:46.326 --> 00:29:50.205
It's seeing Santa's cookies gone.
except a half-eaten one.

575
00:29:50.288 --> 00:29:53.500
Kids pick it up like.
"Santa's teeth touched this."

576
00:29:53.583 --> 00:29:58.254
You're holding on to Christmas past.
This is Christmas future.

577
00:29:58.338 --> 00:30:00.215
Satisfaction guaranteed.

578
00:30:03.468 --> 00:30:04.719
All sales final.

579
00:30:06.012 --> 00:30:08.097
Ha. Silly Gingergoose.

580
00:30:08.181 --> 00:30:10.475
Hello. animal that is not a dog.

581
00:30:10.558 --> 00:30:12.560
Dongle. where have you been?

582
00:30:12.644 --> 00:30:15.355
The usual.
Living the most incredible life.

583
00:30:15.438 --> 00:30:16.397
Who's your friend?

584
00:30:16.481 --> 00:30:18.024
My chisel is my friend.

585
00:30:18.107 --> 00:30:20.235
My sander is my confidant.

586
00:30:20.318 --> 00:30:23.071
This one gave me a ride.
We are not friends.

587
00:30:23.154 --> 00:30:26.366
We're also not enemies.
We're next to each other.

588
00:30:26.449 --> 00:30:30.078
- Any more questions?
- Yeah. where are my hollyberries?

589
00:30:30.161 --> 00:30:33.498
No more questions from you.
But one from Dongle.

590
00:30:33.581 --> 00:30:35.500
Where is the big man?

591
00:30:35.583 --> 00:30:36.876
Uh...

592
00:30:39.337 --> 00:30:41.005
This is all wrong.

593
00:30:41.089 --> 00:30:44.968
Your fellow elves
fighting for recognition is wrong?

594
00:30:45.051 --> 00:30:48.346
No. if anyone loves recognition.
it's Dongle.

595
00:30:49.764 --> 00:30:51.224
You are Dongle.

596
00:30:51.307 --> 00:30:52.976
I recognize you.

597
00:30:53.059 --> 00:30:56.187
Santa does more
than bring toys Dongle makes.

598
00:30:56.271 --> 00:30:59.649
He brings people together.
makes people feel good.

599
00:30:59.732 --> 00:31:00.817
Told you.

600
00:31:00.900 --> 00:31:04.487
The world is changing.
It's time Christmas catches up.

601
00:31:04.571 --> 00:31:06.114
How you sleep at night?

602
00:31:06.197 --> 00:31:07.574
Guilt won't work on me.

603
00:31:07.657 --> 00:31:10.159
Does Dongle look like
a disappointed grandmother?

604
00:31:10.243 --> 00:31:12.745
Simple question. How you go to sleep?

605
00:31:12.829 --> 00:31:15.290
Like every hardworking baby American.

606
00:31:15.373 --> 00:31:18.001
Tucked into a firm swaddle
with a belly full of milk

607
00:31:18.084 --> 00:31:20.461
and a night-night kiss
from Mommy and/or Daddy.

608
00:31:20.545 --> 00:31:23.339
Night-night kiss is unnecessary. no?

609
00:31:23.423 --> 00:31:27.552
You are tired. full. swaddled.
You fall asleep no matter what.

610
00:31:27.635 --> 00:31:30.555
I don't need the kiss. but I like...

611
00:31:30.638 --> 00:31:32.265
Oh. you led me right into that.

612
00:31:32.348 --> 00:31:37.437
Christmas without Santa
is like bedtime without night-night kiss.

613
00:31:37.520 --> 00:31:39.105
No one wants that.

614
00:31:41.733 --> 00:31:44.861
Fine. you're all big elves.
You want Santa back? Go get him.

615
00:31:44.944 --> 00:31:46.529
No. you go.

616
00:31:46.613 --> 00:31:48.531
No chance. Why me?

617
00:31:48.615 --> 00:31:53.870
Because from what you tell Dongle.
the Christmas man. he left in bad shape.

618
00:31:53.953 --> 00:31:59.083
<i>Hollow on the inside.
like a grocery store chocolate nutcracker.</i>

619
00:31:59.167 --> 00:32:02.378
<i>He asks himself. "Who am I anymore?"</i>

620
00:32:02.462 --> 00:32:05.715
Yee-haw. ho. ho.

621
00:32:06.633 --> 00:32:10.219
<i>You break a Santa. you got to fix a Santa.</i>

622
00:32:11.846 --> 00:32:14.599
<i>When you break a Santa this bad.</i>

623
00:32:15.058 --> 00:32:18.436
only one thing
can put his heart back together:

624
00:32:18.519 --> 00:32:22.774
Seeing a bah-humbug stinker like you
find the Christmas spirit.

625
00:32:22.857 --> 00:32:24.359
You will go get Santa.

626
00:32:24.442 --> 00:32:26.319
And what happens if I don't?

627
00:32:26.861 --> 00:32:28.363
Singing.

628
00:32:28.446 --> 00:32:30.239
- Excuse me?
- Hit it.

629
00:32:31.115 --> 00:32:32.450
<i>♪ He's vicious ♪</i>

630
00:32:32.533 --> 00:32:33.785
<i>♪ He's twisted ♪</i>

631
00:32:33.868 --> 00:32:35.745
<i>♪ He's Boss Baby ♪</i>

632
00:32:35.828 --> 00:32:38.790
<i>♪ The baby that ruined
The baby that ruined ♪</i>

633
00:32:38.873 --> 00:32:41.918
<i>♪ The baby that ruined Christmas ♪</i>

634
00:32:42.001 --> 00:32:44.295
Ooh. Catchy hook.

635
00:32:44.379 --> 00:32:47.090
Yeah. throw in some verses and a bridge.

636
00:32:47.173 --> 00:32:50.343
I bet we could get
the whole world singing this.

637
00:32:50.426 --> 00:32:51.386
Please. don't.

638
00:32:52.136 --> 00:32:55.098
<i>♪ He came to the North Pole
And started fussing ♪</i>

639
00:32:55.181 --> 00:32:57.642
<i>♪ Made Santa cry
With all his cussing ♪</i>

640
00:32:57.725 --> 00:33:00.395
<i>♪ He took Father Christmas
All sweet and loved ♪</i>

641
00:33:00.478 --> 00:33:04.232
<i>♪ And showed him just where
He could shove it ♪</i>

642
00:33:06.401 --> 00:33:07.694
<i>♪ He's vicious ♪</i>

643
00:33:07.777 --> 00:33:08.861
<i>♪ He's twisted ♪</i>

644
00:33:08.945 --> 00:33:11.322
<i>♪ He's Boss Baby ♪</i>

645
00:33:11.406 --> 00:33:13.992
<i>♪ The baby that ruined
The baby that ruined ♪</i>

646
00:33:14.075 --> 00:33:16.828
<i>♪ The baby that ruined Christmas ♪</i>

647
00:33:16.911 --> 00:33:18.997
This song makes me wanna dance.

648
00:33:19.080 --> 00:33:21.958
And get rid of our Christmas-ruining baby.

649
00:33:22.500 --> 00:33:25.128
<i>♪ On Christmas morn
All the kids did weep ♪</i>

650
00:33:25.211 --> 00:33:27.714
<i>♪ For not a single toy
Lay beneath their feet ♪</i>

651
00:33:30.258 --> 00:33:33.177
<i>♪ And just in case you forgot his name ♪</i>

652
00:33:33.261 --> 00:33:36.014
<i>♪ The baby who we all should blame ♪</i>

653
00:33:36.097 --> 00:33:38.641
<i>♪ Theodore Leslie Templeton ♪</i>

654
00:33:38.725 --> 00:33:40.935
<i>♪ Shame. shame. shame ♪</i>

655
00:33:41.561 --> 00:33:43.646
<i>♪ Christmas burned down ♪</i>

656
00:33:43.730 --> 00:33:46.607
<i>♪ And he lit the flame ♪</i>

657
00:33:46.691 --> 00:33:48.901
I love this song and hate this baby.

658
00:33:48.985 --> 00:33:50.194
<i>♪ He's vicious ♪</i>

659
00:33:50.278 --> 00:33:51.571
<i>♪ He's twisted ♪</i>

660
00:33:51.654 --> 00:33:53.406
<i>♪ He's Boss Baby ♪</i>

661
00:33:53.489 --> 00:33:56.534
<i>♪ The baby that ruined
The baby that ruined ♪</i>

662
00:33:56.617 --> 00:34:02.915
<i>♪ The baby that ruined Christmas ♪</i>

663
00:34:06.919 --> 00:34:07.754
Fine.

664
00:34:07.837 --> 00:34:11.174
Promise me that song never
leaves this room. and I'll go get him.

665
00:34:11.257 --> 00:34:12.842
But we still have a problem.

666
00:34:14.010 --> 00:34:16.387
I'd get him. but I don't know where he is.

667
00:34:16.471 --> 00:34:17.847
I can find him.

668
00:34:17.930 --> 00:34:20.141
I'm the Noth Pole.

669
00:34:20.224 --> 00:34:22.894
He gives me creepy motel check-in vibes.

670
00:34:22.977 --> 00:34:24.729
Can you really find Santa?

671
00:34:24.812 --> 00:34:27.106
Yes. for a price.

672
00:34:27.190 --> 00:34:29.817
I want the letters to Santa.

673
00:34:29.901 --> 00:34:31.736
- All of them.
- No way.

674
00:34:31.819 --> 00:34:34.906
Santa needs those
to know what every kid wants.

675
00:34:35.531 --> 00:34:38.868
Oh. I'd love to help.
but I'm memorizing children's letters.

676
00:34:38.951 --> 00:34:44.248
If I don't get their requests locked down.
it'll take me weeks to deliver gifts.

677
00:34:45.291 --> 00:34:47.585
Deal. You can have every letter.

678
00:34:47.668 --> 00:34:49.045
What?

679
00:34:51.672 --> 00:34:53.299
That's it. Every letter.

680
00:34:53.382 --> 00:34:55.802
We did our part. You do yours.

681
00:34:58.513 --> 00:35:02.475
The smiling red one lurks
at the mall in your hometown.

682
00:35:03.309 --> 00:35:05.728
I'll remember none of you.

683
00:35:06.312 --> 00:35:07.480
Go.

684
00:35:08.689 --> 00:35:11.901
I can't help it.
One more time. Two. three. four.

685
00:35:11.984 --> 00:35:14.654
<i>♪ The baby that ruined
The baby that ruined ♪</i>

686
00:35:14.737 --> 00:35:17.490
<i>♪ The baby that ruined Christmas ♪</i>

687
00:35:18.324 --> 00:35:19.450
Ron?

688
00:35:20.618 --> 00:35:21.994
You here?

689
00:35:22.078 --> 00:35:23.663
Yo. Ronny.

690
00:35:23.746 --> 00:35:26.749
Santa?

691
00:35:30.128 --> 00:35:31.337
Time to go.

692
00:35:31.420 --> 00:35:32.463
Boss Baby?

693
00:35:33.840 --> 00:35:37.218
But if someone like you would come for me.

694
00:35:37.301 --> 00:35:40.012
it's never too late to change things.

695
00:35:40.096 --> 00:35:44.100
There's no amount of naughtiness
the Christmas spirit can't...

696
00:35:44.183 --> 00:35:48.271
Gonna cut you off before you embarrass
yourself worse than that outfit does.

697
00:35:48.354 --> 00:35:50.773
I'm only here because
if I don't bring you back.

698
00:35:50.857 --> 00:35:54.694
two pint-size hitmakers are gonna
smear my good name all over the Top 40.

699
00:35:54.777 --> 00:35:56.612
Diddly Doo and Lala Doo-Da?

700
00:35:56.696 --> 00:36:00.449
I thought the elves were all mad at me
because of how naughty I've been.

701
00:36:01.534 --> 00:36:02.827
You're not naughty.

702
00:36:02.910 --> 00:36:06.122
just stuck in your ways.
and grossly inefficient.

703
00:36:06.205 --> 00:36:10.376
What do you pay in reindeer maintenance
for one night of use?

704
00:36:10.459 --> 00:36:11.752
Can't you lease?

705
00:36:12.295 --> 00:36:16.716
But for reasons beyond me.
the elves want you back for Christmas.

706
00:36:17.341 --> 00:36:19.552
- And what about you?
- What?

707
00:36:19.635 --> 00:36:22.138
What do you want for Christmas?

708
00:36:24.265 --> 00:36:25.099
No.

709
00:36:27.935 --> 00:36:29.270
No.

710
00:36:29.353 --> 00:36:31.230
Hey. I'm stuck in my ways.

711
00:36:31.314 --> 00:36:35.193
You want something from Santa?
Ask. I don't make the rules.

712
00:36:35.276 --> 00:36:37.445
You absolutely make the...

713
00:36:37.528 --> 00:36:39.322
Fine.

714
00:36:41.949 --> 00:36:43.367
I got it. I got it.

715
00:36:45.536 --> 00:36:48.873
- Come back to the North Pole.
- What. little boy?

716
00:36:48.956 --> 00:36:52.418
I'd like you
to come back to the North Pole.

717
00:36:53.044 --> 00:36:54.795
Santa can do that for you.

718
00:36:57.006 --> 00:37:01.344
I think we just had
a Christmas spirit breakthrough.

719
00:37:01.427 --> 00:37:03.554
Is this what it feels like?

720
00:37:04.096 --> 00:37:06.724
I also want a tie clip.
a gold one with wings on it.

721
00:37:06.807 --> 00:37:10.811
And one of those electric shoe polishers
you see in golf club locker rooms.

722
00:37:10.895 --> 00:37:14.774
And gift cards. They're tacky.
but it's like plastic money.

723
00:37:15.358 --> 00:37:17.526
That's what the Christmas spirit is.

724
00:37:17.610 --> 00:37:20.821
Asking for things you don't need
and don't have time to get.

725
00:37:20.905 --> 00:37:22.865
- No.
- Well. hey. you tried.

726
00:37:25.368 --> 00:37:26.994
Ho. ho. ho!

727
00:37:29.497 --> 00:37:31.624
You have the worst catchphrase.

728
00:37:31.707 --> 00:37:33.709
Yeah? What's yours?

729
00:37:33.793 --> 00:37:37.838
Oh. I was trying to make
"fart poop doody" work. but...

730
00:37:37.922 --> 00:37:39.715
Do your dumb laugh.

731
00:37:39.799 --> 00:37:41.217
Ho. ho. ho!

732
00:37:45.972 --> 00:37:47.390
You've been busy.

733
00:37:47.473 --> 00:37:48.641
Santa. I'm sorry.

734
00:37:48.724 --> 00:37:51.352
It was everyone else
who messed with all the stuff...

735
00:37:51.435 --> 00:37:53.020
- I like it.
- I helped.

736
00:37:55.731 --> 00:37:57.942
Dongle. It's jolly to see you.

737
00:37:58.025 --> 00:38:01.195
Dongle is a comforting presence.

738
00:38:01.279 --> 00:38:03.281
A gift from all of us.

739
00:38:03.364 --> 00:38:06.033
But don't worry. Dongle made it.

740
00:38:06.117 --> 00:38:08.911
A Baby Corp monitor? Um...

741
00:38:08.995 --> 00:38:10.997
Press the talky button.

742
00:38:11.080 --> 00:38:12.832
<i>I'm Baby Corp.</i>

743
00:38:12.915 --> 00:38:14.500
<i>I'm incompetent.</i>

744
00:38:17.878 --> 00:38:20.756
<i>First rule of business. I'm dumb.</i>

745
00:38:20.840 --> 00:38:24.385
<i>Second rule. I forgot. because I'm dumb.</i>

746
00:38:30.725 --> 00:38:32.184
Look at the bottom.

747
00:38:33.019 --> 00:38:33.936
"Dongle"?

748
00:38:34.020 --> 00:38:36.105
We put our names on everything.

749
00:38:36.188 --> 00:38:40.318
so the children know why they weep
with joy when they get a Dongle toy.

750
00:38:40.401 --> 00:38:43.988
It's not the way things
have always been done. but...

751
00:38:44.071 --> 00:38:48.701
If the way things are always done
leaves people unhappy. who needs it?

752
00:38:57.460 --> 00:39:01.255
It's perfect. I'm sorry
I didn't think of this years ago.

753
00:39:01.339 --> 00:39:03.507
Anyone know if this is edible?

754
00:39:03.591 --> 00:39:04.842
It's that late?

755
00:39:04.925 --> 00:39:06.469
It's not edible.

756
00:39:06.552 --> 00:39:09.138
We don't have time. What have I done?

757
00:39:09.221 --> 00:39:11.932
I'll never get the presents out tonight.

758
00:39:12.016 --> 00:39:14.852
Is this guy's name Santa or Can't-a?

759
00:39:14.935 --> 00:39:18.147
Efficiency. Ron.
Still got those gifts memorized?

760
00:39:18.230 --> 00:39:20.149
Do I? TWCAFIJ.

761
00:39:20.232 --> 00:39:23.861
Tim Wants Canadian
Action Figure in Jacuzzi.

762
00:39:23.944 --> 00:39:24.987
He's got them.

763
00:39:25.071 --> 00:39:27.239
Yeah!

764
00:39:27.865 --> 00:39:29.492
Elves. Baby Corp.

765
00:39:29.575 --> 00:39:31.243
let's Christmas.

766
00:39:33.079 --> 00:39:36.248
- Like "let's do this" but...
- We got it. We just don't like it.

767
00:39:36.874 --> 00:39:38.918
Let's Christmas.

768
00:39:39.001 --> 00:39:41.128
Yeah!

769
00:39:48.302 --> 00:39:49.595
Release.

770
00:39:56.102 --> 00:39:57.061
- Toys.
- Toys.

771
00:39:57.144 --> 00:39:58.020
- Toys.
- Toys.

772
00:40:11.492 --> 00:40:15.162
I'd like your most expensive pinky ring.

773
00:40:15.246 --> 00:40:17.790
Let's just say I've got enough letters

774
00:40:17.873 --> 00:40:21.293
to fill vending machines
from Miyazaki to Hokkaido.

775
00:40:21.377 --> 00:40:22.253
What?

776
00:40:22.336 --> 00:40:23.796
No. no. no.

777
00:40:25.423 --> 00:40:27.675
<i>Dear Noth. stop selling letters.</i>

778
00:40:27.758 --> 00:40:28.801
<i>It's not nice.</i>

779
00:40:28.884 --> 00:40:31.303
<i>Here's a present. anyway. Love. Tim.</i>

780
00:40:33.639 --> 00:40:37.560
The scary broken toy
I wanted as a kid. but never got.

781
00:40:38.727 --> 00:40:40.813
Mom. Dad?

782
00:40:41.397 --> 00:40:42.398
It's Kyle.

783
00:40:42.481 --> 00:40:47.153
<i>A ten-speed bicycle from
Ding Dong Dongle. and it's made from wood.</i>

784
00:40:47.236 --> 00:40:49.613
<i>Jingly Jangly made my teddy bear.</i>

785
00:40:49.697 --> 00:40:51.365
<i>A baseball mitt.</i>

786
00:40:51.449 --> 00:40:54.160
<i>And Tippy Tappy Sloppy the Elf made it.</i>

787
00:40:55.536 --> 00:40:59.874
Lucky the kids got Mom's genetics.
because Dad is a pile of yikes.

788
00:40:59.957 --> 00:41:00.958
Santa?

789
00:41:02.751 --> 00:41:04.628
A yo-yo.

790
00:41:04.712 --> 00:41:08.007
Made by PoopyDoopy the Elf?

791
00:41:08.090 --> 00:41:10.301
Thank you. Santa and PoopyDoopy.

792
00:41:10.384 --> 00:41:14.013
I love it.
and promise to share with everyone.

793
00:41:14.096 --> 00:41:15.931
How do we get past the kid?

794
00:41:20.019 --> 00:41:22.229
You sick St. Nick.

795
00:41:26.317 --> 00:41:29.111
I can't believe
I delivered presents with Santa.

796
00:41:29.195 --> 00:41:30.821
Every last one.

797
00:41:30.905 --> 00:41:32.740
Free of charge.

798
00:41:32.823 --> 00:41:34.408
Oh. please. I helped.

799
00:41:34.492 --> 00:41:37.453
Doesn't mean I'll dump my portfolio
and move to a commune.

800
00:41:37.536 --> 00:41:38.704
Thank you. Santa.

801
00:41:39.330 --> 00:41:40.831
Merry Christmas.

802
00:41:43.918 --> 00:41:45.920
So. what lame teachable gift

803
00:41:46.003 --> 00:41:49.548
that sums up this whole experience
do you have for me?

804
00:41:50.090 --> 00:41:50.925
Santa?

805
00:41:51.509 --> 00:41:52.468
Hello?

806
00:41:52.551 --> 00:41:53.552
Nothing?

807
00:41:53.636 --> 00:41:56.388
Don't you want me
to get the Christmas spir...? Ow!

808
00:41:56.472 --> 00:41:58.474
Ho. ho. ho.

809
00:42:01.227 --> 00:42:03.229
They call me MC Christmas.

810
00:42:03.312 --> 00:42:05.940
The C also stands for Christmas.

811
00:42:06.023 --> 00:42:08.442
- Ted. it's Christmas morning.
- What?

812
00:42:08.526 --> 00:42:12.947
We forgot to make snack leis.
We'll starve during fruitcake hockey.

813
00:42:13.030 --> 00:42:18.160
We'll ruin our sweet little guy's
first traditional Templeton Christmas.

814
00:42:18.244 --> 00:42:21.330
What if he isn't into
the traditional Templeton Christmas?

815
00:42:21.413 --> 00:42:24.583
They're family traditions.
Our family's different now.

816
00:42:24.667 --> 00:42:28.045
If the way we always do things
makes one of us unhappy.

817
00:42:28.128 --> 00:42:29.880
let's do different things.

818
00:42:32.466 --> 00:42:35.928
- I could come up with new ideas.
- Family brainstorm.

819
00:42:36.011 --> 00:42:38.681
What are fun words
that rhyme with "wreath"?

820
00:42:38.764 --> 00:42:41.684
Santa gave me snack leis.
so this tradition is back on.

821
00:42:41.767 --> 00:42:44.311
Fruitcake hockey in the driveway.

822
00:42:44.395 --> 00:42:47.189
- We'll get the sticks.
- Wrap the baby in sofa cushions.

823
00:42:47.273 --> 00:42:48.857
Your mom plays violent.

824
00:42:50.693 --> 00:42:52.152
I'll talk them out of that.

825
00:42:53.404 --> 00:42:55.990
You don't have
to throw out every tradition for me.

826
00:42:56.073 --> 00:42:58.367
You'll do fruitcake hockey and snack leis?

827
00:42:58.450 --> 00:43:00.786
This wearable choking hazard? No.

828
00:43:00.869 --> 00:43:04.582
But I'll play
your holiday dessert Canadian stick game.

829
00:43:04.665 --> 00:43:06.333
- You will?
- It's nonsense.

830
00:43:06.417 --> 00:43:11.755
But it can't be all bad if it brings
people together. and gets you all smiley.

831
00:43:11.839 --> 00:43:13.090
Just like Santa.

832
00:43:13.173 --> 00:43:16.927
I guess. I mean. if you squint
and don't think about it...

833
00:43:17.011 --> 00:43:19.638
No. Feeling Christmas spirit.

834
00:43:24.810 --> 00:43:26.395
Goal!

835
00:43:27.354 --> 00:43:30.482
I got a sock full of dead dinosaurs.

836
00:43:30.566 --> 00:43:33.235
Merry Christmas to all.

837
00:43:33.319 --> 00:43:35.112
The end.

838
00:43:36.989 --> 00:43:39.533
That was in no way
a "make us fall asleep" story.

839
00:43:39.617 --> 00:43:41.869
- I have so many questions.
- Yeah.

840
00:43:41.952 --> 00:43:46.165
Wasn't your setup about why we should do
goofy traditions even if we don't want to?

841
00:43:46.248 --> 00:43:48.208
You bailed on that with your brother.

842
00:43:48.292 --> 00:43:52.087
- Then he did some. but not others.
- What's the takeaway?

843
00:43:52.171 --> 00:43:54.715
Want easy lessons? Go to kindergarten.

844
00:43:54.798 --> 00:43:57.676
- Can I?
- Not until you're 5. Go to sleep.

845
00:43:57.760 --> 00:43:58.594
- Five?
- How?

846
00:43:58.677 --> 00:44:01.639
You opened a Pandora's box
of moral ambiguity.

847
00:44:01.722 --> 00:44:04.850
Can we go to the zoo
if I don't make fun of the capybaras?

848
00:44:07.061 --> 00:44:08.812
You grew up big and weird.

849
00:44:16.987 --> 00:44:19.531
Okay. all done. Dongle kill kids.

850
00:44:19.615 --> 00:44:21.158
Very funny.

851
00:44:21.241 --> 00:44:24.078
Fool me once. shame on you.
Fool me twice...

852
00:44:24.161 --> 00:44:26.622
Dongle is serious.
The big one deserved it.

853
00:44:26.705 --> 00:44:29.333
She stopped feeding
the Christmas Panda and it died.

854
00:44:29.416 --> 00:44:30.501
What?

855
00:44:32.503 --> 00:44:35.547
Dongle tricked you again for drama.

856
00:44:36.256 --> 00:44:38.884
You are welcome for the spice of life.

857
00:44:38.967 --> 00:44:40.427
Merry Christmas.

858
00:44:40.511 --> 00:44:42.388
Merry Christmas.

859
00:45:06.412 --> 00:45:08.247
<i>♪ Boss Baby ♪</i>

